$29 \to 88 \to 44 \
to 22 \to 11$. That’s 4 steps. $T(11)=14$. So $T(29) = 4 + 14 = 18$. Correct.
And the chain from 127 to 29 is 29 steps? Let’s recount.
127, 382, 191, 574, 287, 862, 431, 1294, 647, 1942, 971, 2914, 1457, 4372, 2186, 1093, 3280, 1640, 820, 410, 205, 616, 308, 154, 77, 232, 116, 58, 29.
