So 127 is not a record-setter. It’s a short chain. My intuition about Mersenne primes being long was wrong. 127 collapses quickly. It feeds into 29, which is a short chain.




So what feeds into the long chains? 41 feeds into 23. 23 is short. But the path from 41 to 23 is long. It’s the primes in between that sustain the length. 31, 47, 71, 107, 137, 167, 251, 283, 433, 593, 719, 1367, 1619, 2051, 2429, 3077, 577, 433... It’s a long, winding road of primes.

